---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Contact | Wampus Labs" description="Talk with Wampus Labs about IT, automation, digital signage, or custom software.">
  <section class="page-hero section"><div class="container narrow">
    <p class="eyebrow">Contact</p><h1>What are you trying to fix, improve, or build?</h1>
    <p>You don’t need a polished project brief. A quick note about what’s going on is enough to start.</p>
  </div></section>
  <section class="section contact-section"><div class="container contact-grid">
    <div class="contact-card"><p class="eyebrow">Email</p><h2><a href="mailto:hello@wampuslabs.com">hello@wampuslabs.com</a></h2><p>Tell us what’s getting in the way and the best way to reach you. We’ll take it from there.</p></div>
    <aside class="contact-expectations"><h2>What happens next?</h2><ol>
      <li><span>1</span><p><strong>We read your note.</strong> A real person.</p></li>
      <li><span>2</span><p><strong>We ask a few questions.</strong> Just enough to understand the problem.</p></li>
      <li><span>3</span><p><strong>We suggest a next step.</strong> No pressure and no mystery package.</p></li>
    </ol></aside>
  </div></section>
</BaseLayout>
